<h2 id="2-tty-clock">2. tty-clock</h2>

<p>Displays a simple digital clock on the terminal.</p>

<p>To install:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">git clone https://github.com/xorg62/tty-clock.git
<span class="nb">cd </span>tty-clock
<span class="nb">sudo </span>make <span class="nb">install</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Then run <code class="highlighter-rouge">tty-clock</code> on the terminal if you want to leave in the center run with the parameter <code class="highlighter-rouge">-c</code> <code class="highlighter-rouge">tty-clock -c</code>, to exit press <code class="highlighter-rouge">q</code>. For more information and parameters refer to page 1 of the manual: <code class="highlighter-rouge">man 1 tty-clock</code>.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/wm/tty-clock.png" alt="tty-clock" /></p>

<p>Useful link for <code class="highlighter-rouge">tty-clock</code></p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/xorg62/tty-clock">https://github.com/xorg62/tty-clock</a></li>
</ul>

