<h2 id="3-neofetch-with-images">3. Neofetch with images</h2>

<p>Displays image in neofetch instead of ASCII characters.</p>

<p>After installing Neofetch via your package manager, also install the w3m package, examples:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">emerge w3m <span class="c"># Gentoo, Funtoo, Sabayon, ...</span>
apt <span class="nb">install </span>w3m <span class="c"># Debian, Ubuntu, Mint, ...</span>
pacman <span class="nt">-S</span> w3m <span class="c"># Arch, Manjaro, Antergos, ...</span></code></pre></figure>

<p>Then edit the neofetch configuration file: <code class="highlighter-rouge">vim ~/.config/neofetch/config.conf</code> then look for the line with the term: <code class="highlighter-rouge">image_backend</code>, if you canâ€™t find it add it to w3m: <code class="highlighter-rouge">image_backend="w3m"</code>. Also change the line with the term <code class="highlighter-rouge">image_source</code> and assign your image path: <code class="highlighter-rouge">image_source="/path/to/image.png"</code>, if you want your Wallpaper to appear, give the word wallpaper: <code class="highlighter-rouge">image_source="wallpaper"</code></p>

<p>Turn the neofetch.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/wm/tty-clock.png" alt="tty-clock" /></p>

<p>Useful link for <code class="highlighter-rouge">neofetch</code></p>
<ul>
  <li><a href="https://github.com/dylanaraps/neofetch">https://github.com/dylanaraps/neofetch</a></li>
</ul>

