<h2 id="4-pacmansh">4. pacman.sh</h2>

<p>Download the code: <code class="highlighter-rouge">wget http://bit.ly/pacmansh -O pacman.sh</code>, make it executable <code class="highlighter-rouge">chmod +x pacman.sh</code>, run it: ./pacman.sh. If you want it to appear every time you open the terminal, run the commands below:</p>

<p>For BASH:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">mv </span>pacman.sh ~/.local/share/
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s1">'$HOME/.local/share/pacman.sh'</span> <span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> ~/.bashrc</code></pre></figure>

<p>For ZSH:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">mv </span>pacman.sh ~/.local/share/
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s1">'$HOME/.local/share/pacman.sh'</span> <span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> ~/.zshrc</code></pre></figure>

<p>For FISH:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="nb">mv </span>pacman.sh ~/.local/share/
<span class="nb">echo</span> <span class="s1">'$HOME/.local/share/pacman.sh'</span> <span class="o">&gt;&gt;</span> ~/.config/fish/config.fish</code></pre></figure>

<p><img src="/assets/img/wm/pacman.sh.png" alt="pacman.sh" /></p>

